issue.title: `oneOf` / `anyOf` usage with form-based content-type schema
issue.body:
_Originally posted by @jacobjmarks in https://github.com/swagger-api/swagger-ui/issues/3803#issuecomment-965940166_

I am having a similar issue here. See below an example spec in which I am attempting to describe a form which can accept one of two possible schemas:

``` yaml
openapi: 3.0.1
info:
  title: FooBar
  version: 1.0.0
paths:
  /foobar:
    post:
      summary: Summary
      requestBody:
        content:
          application/x-www-form-urlencoded:
            schema:
              oneOf:
              - type: object
                properties:
                  Foo:
                    type: string
              - type: object
                properties:
                  Bar:
                    type: string
      responses:
        default:
          description: Description
```

> Please note that the same issue occurs when using a `requestBody/content` type of `multipart/form-data`

This endpoint should expect to receive a body of either `Foo=` or `Bar=`.
This schema causes the following Swagger UI interface to be rendered:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/19641427/141227881-e80d3805-af76-4451-9810-3f03fbb75938.png)

This is _not_ correct. It is representing the form as a JSON payload and causes invalid requests to be sent to the endpoint in which the Swagger UI is encoding each character as a separate form value. E.g. sending a value of `hi` would result in the body `0=h&1=i`.

This same issue occurs when using `anyOf`.

When using `allOf`, however, a correct representation is rendered as below:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/19641427/141227963-19f881e9-90fb-4bf3-bda8-299bdae3836f.png)

Are there any updates here regarding the support for such `oneOf` and `anyOf` usage? Alternatively; am I incorrectly defining my schema in some way to achieve such usage?

comment.body: This could be a great feature

issue.title: SwaggerUI not able to pass api_key in header
issue.body:
When reporting a bug, please provide the following details:
- swagger-ui version = SwaggerUI 2.2.6
- a swagger file reproducing the issue = See below.

In my Swagger file, I have my api_key defined as a header parameter.

```
    "securityDefinitions": {
        "api_key": {
            "type": "apiKey",
            "name": "api_key",
            "in": "header"
        }
    },
```

When I am pulling it up on SwaggerUI, the authorize button is able to read it and show cases the following: 
![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/9384995/20243083/15717784-a905-11e6-933a-ddb5eb4c9d10.png)

However, when I am clicking on "Try-it" button, it is not sending in the "api_key" header. Instead here is how the request goes out: 

```
OPTIONS /api-url HTTP/1.1
Host: api-host.com
Connection: keep-alive
Access-Control-Request-Method: POST
Origin: http://localhost:8080
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.3; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/54.0.2840.71 Safari/537.36
Access-Control-Request-Headers: api_key, content-type
Accept: */*
Referer: http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui-2.2.6/dist/?url=http://localhost:8080/swagger.json
Accept-Encoding: gzip, deflate, sdch
Accept-Language: en-US,en;q=0.8
```

Note: It sends the header field `api_key` as a value of `Access-Control-Request-Headers` instead of sending something like `api_key=ABCD` as the server is expecting.

On the server side I can see that the requests are failing because the expected "api_key" header is missing and it is throwing an HTTP 401 which I get back on the client.

Please advise if this is a bug or am I missing something.

issue.title: How to pass a header value on click of the 'Try it out' button on the Swagger UI page?
issue.body: I am creating a web API which takes in a API key header parameter. Can I pass the header value on click of the 'Try it out' button? For applications consuming this API they will need to pass the header, but for the Swagger UI testing page I want to be able to pass the API key from the swagger UI js fie. Any help?
